  , issueTitle =
      "Missing Last-Modified and ETag headers for joined files"
  , issuePullRequest = Nothing
  , issueUrl =
      URL "https://api.github.com/repos/jsdelivr/jsdelivr/issues/524"
  , issueCreatedAt = 2014 (-03) (-28) 13 : 43 : 49 UTC
  , issueBody =
      Just
        "If I try to get a single file I can see Last-Modified and ETag headers, for example:\n\n```\n$ curl -I http://cdn.jsdelivr.net/jquery/2.1.0/jquery.min.js\nHTTP/1.1 200 OK\nServer: nginx/1.4.3\nDate: Fri, 28 Mar 2014 13:37:13 GMT\nContent-Type: application/javascript\nContent-Length: 83615\nConnection: keep-alive\nLast-Modified: Fri, 24 Jan 2014 22:20:40 GMT\nETag: \"52e2e738-1469f\"\nAccess-Control-Allow-Origin: *\nCache-Control: public, max-age=31536000\nVary: Accept-Encoding\nX-Cache: HIT\nPOP: prome-it\nAccept-Ranges: bytes\n```\n\nBut if I make a request joining many files together both headers are missing (and this drives to complete re-download of the entire file on each request):\n\n```\n$ curl -I http://cdn.jsdelivr.net/g/jquery@2.1.0,angularjs@1.2.14\\(angular.min.js+angular-resource.min.js+angular-animate.min.js+angular-cookies.min.js+angular-route.min.js+angular-sanitize.min.js\\)\nHTTP/1.1 200 OK\nServer: nginx/1.4.3\nDate: Fri, 28 Mar 2014 13:37:53 GMT\nContent-Type: application/javascript\nConnection: keep-alive\nCache-Control: public, max-age=15724800\nVary: Accept-Encoding\nAccess-Control-Allow-Origin: *\nX-Cache: MISS\nPOP: prome-it\n```\n\n(the problem is present for both http AND https requests)\n\nIs it possible to provide those headers also for joined files? It would be amazing to avoid to do many times the same request using browser's cache mechanisms.\n\nThank you\n"
